The holiday is not united in the EU and America.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes national and state holidays and public holidays.
Public holidays are mostly linked to church holidays and outstanding historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are public holidays - the latter only so that New Year's Evemakers can rest.
We have a total of 11 red letters all year round.
National holiday is also the Memorial Day of the 1956 Revolution, which commemorates the Revolution of 1848 and 23 October.
On August 20th, we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1st, and on November 1st and 2nd, we remember our relatives and friends who died.
In addition, Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas are two-day holidays.
Since our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on the weekend according to the calendar, it has become a practice to move the working day in cases where we would only work for one day before or after the red-letter holiday.
True, the price of extended weekends is that we do not stay away from work-school on the previous Saturdays.
