This is when one of the harmonica foldable boards was violated by a stuck cable in a length of about 1 m.
In order to avoid further damage, the opening of the board was not continued.
Astronauts were originally tasked with taking a check-up walk from the Discovery shuttle and then repairing another solar panel with a malfunctioning rotational system. Instead, they had to devote their entire time to repairing the damaged solar panel.
Scott Parazynski was chosen to do the stunt on the 30-metre robot arm attached to the crane of the station.
