Congress approves the takeover of MiFID, which came into force on November 1
In parallel with the parliamentary process, which ended today with a congressional vote approving Senate amendments, the government initiated a social dialogue on the regulation on which the law was based, so that both could enter into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the different groups unanimously highlighted the efforts of Members and Senators in negotiations and agreements to develop the most favourable normative protection for investors and to regulate the activities of companies in detail in order to operate effectively on the market.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, allows for the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, broadening the supervisory rights of the Spanish National Securities Market Committee (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new directive enables financial advisory services for specialised companies, but also for natural or legal persons, as well as for securities distribution companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies, to establish a new form of financial services company (ESIS), namely financial advisory companies (AFIs).
In addition, the law increases the number of systems capable of carrying out operations involving funds, thus adding multilateral trading platforms and internalisation systems for the execution of orders to regulated secondary markets, which compete with current stock exchanges.
In addition, the Act requires investment service providers to provide market information on the defining aspects of their business profile, risk taking and risk management methods, and to keep records of all operations carried out in order to facilitate the control of CNMV.
The Congress Economic Committee has introduced a number of amendments. Among these, it is of paramount importance that securitised debts are treated as "complex" funds due to the high risk to the investor. This has been proven in connection with U.S. high-risk mortgage lending (subprime).
On the other hand, the transposition of the directive was also used to legally outline the scope of activities of those with economic and business qualifications, 30 years after the royal decree defining professional functions that could only be carried out by economists came into force in 1977.
And the Senate has proposed the creation of new players in the financial sector, such as an intermediary agent who works for another account, does not need the permission of CNMV, and can sell products or acquire customers to several investment companies at the same time.
