What insurance is right for me?
Vehicle insurance, which means safety for the owner of the car against various damage events, is significant and depends on several factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining the driver's license, marital status, type and nature of the car to be insured.
Buying a car is just the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car you want.
First of all, we need to be aware of what this is about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company undertakes to compensate for the fixed insurance premium in the event of the event of the damage.
The insurance premium is practically the amount paid for insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining a driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured, its use, and others.
Insurance companies determine the premium on the basis of statistics, i.e. a higher amount is paid by those who represent a higher risk of accidents.
That’s why women over the age of 25 or pay less, as statistics show that they pose a lower risk because they are more cautious.
Similarly, according to the statements, insurance companies concluded that married people also cause fewer accidents than lonely people.
For the type of use of the car, frequency is decisive.
More frequent use increases the possibility of an accident.
When determining the insurance premium, insurance companies take into account a number of factors.
Therefore, the owner should carefully look into it so that he can choose the most suitable form of insurance for his profile.
In the following, we present the most important factors in choosing to best adapt to the needs of the insured and to set an acceptable price.
When concluding an insurance contract, people under the age of 25 have to face a number of disadvantages, such as lack of driving experience and the freshness of their driving licence.
Although it is ideal to be assured against all dangers, there are also more economical solutions.
Precautionary drivers can take out complete insurance with themselves, thus ensuring against all dangers, and the price will be affordable.
For this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
“The amount of the self-insurance to be paid by the insured depends on the premium; the higher the premium, the lower the self-insurance,” says Luis Noguera, head of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended liability insurance for third parties when the customer provides himself against damage to others, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, you will be insured against theft, fire damage and loss of the car.
A word of advice.
If you are not 25 years old, be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus and you can reduce the amount to be paid in the future.
Bonuses are called discounts compared to the basic tariff of the insurance company.
Compared to the basic tariff, the penalty is called malus.
“The amount of the bonus and the ralus depends on the insurance company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year, you can afford to increase the bonus,” explains Noguera.
Once the age of 25 has been exceeded, it is easier for owners to get adequate insurance, as the risk of accidents is reduced thanks to the experience gained over the years.
Then we advise you to take full insurance with you.
"In general, young people are not yet able to apply their experience properly in an accident or even when driving," says the director of the European insurance company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when drivers have already overcome the fear of beginners.
If the insured person is already married, but they do not have children yet, it is best to take out complete insurance, of course, if his financial opportunities allow it.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children to be the least risky customers, so the fee to be paid is also lower in their case.
In this case, it is best to own a complete insurance (this can reach up to EUR 300) or, if they have a higher bonus, extend the insurance to the damage caused to others from the third year of the vehicle.
"They drive more calmly, but at the same time they have more purchasing power and can afford to have a higher share," Luis Noguera said.
In the case of pensioners, we recommend full insurance (around 150 euros) or in the case of a higher bonus it can be extended to liability insurance.
Car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it provides protection to the owner in the event of damage events, but also because it is a large expense, so it is essential to choose the personalized form of insurance properly.
