United Internet will be a major shareholder in Versatel
United Internet has secured more than 20 percent of its stake in Versatel telecommunications.
As the company said on Wednesday, the average price per share is 14.46 Euros.
This represents 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There were speculations about the takeover before that.
The possibility of increasing ownership in Versailles remains open.
With this step, they want to promote the consolidation of the German DSL market, United Internet said.
Prior to this, on Wednesday, there were assumptions about a possible involvement, after Berenberg Bank increased its share of the network service provider in Düsseldorf by an additional 5 percent to 15.1%.
The financial institution only maintains the share to a third party, it is reported in the financial market.
On the previous day, United Internet already owned a narrow 10% of the Drillisch mobile phone company.
Within the framework of a capital increase, Drillisch placed 17.4 million new shares worth EUR 106.4 million.
Of these, United Internet purchased 5.15 million shares for EUR 31.4 million.
In addition, the companies initiated a dialogue on cooperation on the launch of DSL and mobile phone products.
“We are strengthening our partnership,” a United-Internet spokesperson said.
The two companies jointly founded the MSP joint venture to take over the competing Freenet.
In the beginning, the two companies are satisfied with a good ten percent stake in Freenet and do not exercise the right to take over another 18.49 percent of Freenet, United Internet said on Thursday.
However, the two companies remain open to all possibilities, especially with regard to increasing the shareholding in Freenet AG.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on the strategic partnership were concluded in mid-November.
The poker game around Freenet, which has been held for months and is only a matter-of-fact game, is part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million contract mobile phone customers and 1.27 million DSL and fixed access customers.
United Internet and the holding company Drillisch have so far held a direct 6.01 percent stake in Freenet.
Now it has been agreed that Drillisch will bring in another four percent.
